dcterms:creator: M. L. Rosenzweig
R. H. MacArthur
dcterms:description: The Rosenzweig-MacArthur Predator-Prey Model provides a standard framework to study the coupled dynamics of predator and prey populations, predicting sustained oscillations in their populations.
dcterms:title: Rosenzweig-MacArthur Predator-Prey Model

dcterms:creator: D. T. Gillespie
dcterms:description: The Gillespie Algorithm is used for the exact stochastic simulation of coupled chemical reactions, which can be applied to simulate the stochastic dynamics of the Rosenzweig-MacArthur model.
dcterms:title: Gillespie Algorithm

dcterms:creator: C. W. Gardiner
dcterms:description: The Van Kampen System Size Expansion is a method used to analyze stochastic processes in large systems, which is relevant for understanding the dynamics of the stochastic Rosenzweig-MacArthur model.
dcterms:title: Van Kampen System Size Expansion

dcterms:creator: C. W. Gardiner
dcterms:description: The Fokker-Planck Equation describes the time evolution of probability distributions of stochastic processes, which is used to analyze the stochastic dynamics of the Rosenzweig-MacArthur model.
dcterms:title: Fokker-Planck Equation

dcterms:creator: N. R. Smith
B. Meerson
dcterms:description: The Stochastic RMA Model extends the Rosenzweig-MacArthur model to include demographic stochasticity, analyzing its effects on population oscillations.
dcterms:title: Stochastic RMA Model
